<br>
Scintilation can, or could until the last patch -and it is 99.99% sure they wouldn't have changed it without saying it first-, hit at least 26 lvl43+ mobs at the same time...that was my best AoE nuke, ever <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Out of 26 mobs 2 were fully resisted and i had a couple partial resists but it is normal given the number of resist test...<br>
<br>
Thanks for the compliment Waldena. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Scintilation takes a little bit more than 2 secondes to cast 3 secondes actually and the recast time is about 0.5 - 1 secondes after the spells have refreshed once you have casted the 1st scintil.<br>
<br>
Reilnkur - Scintilation has a shorter range than wiz AE spells, for instance, so be sure to stand in the middle of the crowd...it is funnier and also more efficiant <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (yeah, i've seen a few mages who were too scared to do it and prefered to stay far away from the fight to use DD <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Teramenor - There isn't only one tactic for AE groups, it depends of the ppl avaiable to group and the areas where you are hunting. As a rule you will need a puller, a cleric(preferably lvl54+ for hero+marzin), an enchanter(lvl52+ for the AE stun, lvl54+ for c2 if possible) and 3 AE casters.<br>
Among the AErs : <br>
_wiz are the best for the AE phase (eg. NUKE NUKE NUKE!!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
_magicians are the next best, and running very close second imho, for direct fire power. I would suggest to take 1 or 2 mages at least so that the pets will take care of the 2 - 3 mobs left at 10% life after the AEing and of the possible repops.<br>
_druids are especially good in place which are considered outdoor (eg. Karnor Castle)...trust me on this, you REALLY appreciate the speed difference between a lvl50+ SoW and the Jboots when you have 20+ mobs chasing you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Having a back up healer for the cleric and the enchanter is nice too.<br>
_a 2nd cleric is possible and works well...it greatly speed up the buffing phase (while the group get ready) and it's also safer for the enchanter and other cleric. Clerics also have a PBAE spell (upvheal -sp?-) and are generally over the moon to be able to use it vs 15+ mobs...be careful though, some are too shocked to do so much damages and just pass out <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
A few AE rules :<br>
_ALWAYS do it with a lvl52 enchanter to stun...even a shaman with AE tigir won't be enough against more than 10 mobs. My personal record without an enchanter to stun is 10 sebilis frogs (4mages, 1 necro, 1 clr)...we won, no one died but we everyone ended up between 01% and 30% life (i was the one at 1% because i had to use my Shiny Brass Idol -1 charge of divine aura- to survive <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
_If the cleric has it, FORCE him to death pact everyone...it only cost 600mana and 6 pearls and it WILL save lives, and maybe the group, at least one time out of three.<br>
_They are more rules but my pause time is running out in RL <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It is funnier if you learn them by yourself anyway <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
My groups are a bit special because i am (next to) always the puller and as a consequence we have enough spots for four AoE casters in it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
A the level 51 i suggest you to try Karnor to AE rather than sebilis, mobs are a bit lower there (meaning lower resists) but all will be blue at least till the lvl54...<br>
<br>
